    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect NTN k-offset calculation in time alignment\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_time_alignment()` function in the NR UE MAC was not behaving as expected due to incorrect NTN k-offset calculations. The NTN offset was being exponentially scaled by the subcarrier spacing value (2^scs), causing incorrect frame and slot calculations for time alignment.\n\nThis fix corrects the NTN offset calculation by removing the erroneous scaling operation and using the k_offset value directly as a slot offset.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_procedures.c`: Modified `set_time_alignment()` to directly use `cell_specific_k_offset` instead of calling `GET_NTN_UE_K_OFFSET()` \n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/mac_defs.h`: Fixed `GET_NTN_UE_K_OFFSET()` macro to return k_offset directly without `<< scs` scaling\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/mac_defs.h`: Updated `GET_DURATION_RX_TO_TX()` function to also use k_offset directly\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running NTN simulations with non-zero k_offset values, the UE would incorrectly calculate transmission timing, leading to missed uplink transmissions and RAR windows being scheduled at wrong frames/slots. The issue becomes more pronounced with higher SCS values where the incorrect 2^scs scaling results in extremely large offset values.\n"
}